fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.design

Interface IPageRouteResolver

  • Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @PluginService
 @FunctionalInterface
public interface IPageRouteResolver
    Provides custom URI resolution, overriding default rules for determining which page is mapped to a specific URL.

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be immutable and therefore completely thread-safe.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      IAuthenticatedPage resolve(IAuthenticatedPage page, IDesignService designService, ITicket ticket, IHttpServiceCall call)

    • Method Detail

      • resolve

        IAuthenticatedPage resolve(IAuthenticatedPage page,
                           IDesignService designService,
                           ITicket ticket,
                           IHttpServiceCall call)
        Resolves the URI of a call address as an authenticated page.

        If this resolver defines (or redefines) the returned page, it may be relevant to define (or redefine) the routeContext attribute.

        Parameters:
        page - the preselected page, either selected by default or by another registered instance of IPageRouteResolver with higher priority. May be null.
        designService - the design service, providing access to available pages for the authenticated user.
        ticket - the ticket obtained from the call, providing access to the authenticated user.
        call - the call being routed to the page service.
        Returns:
        either the unmodified page parameter, or null (if this resolver does not need to change the currently-selected page), or an alternative page (or a proxy page implementation).
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IPageRouter.resolve(IHttpServiceCall)
